@startuml Inventory Service - Pipes and Filters Architecture

!theme cerulean-outline
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title Inventory Service - Pipes and Filters Processing Pipeline

' Define the pipes (data channels) and filters (processing components)
participant "📥 order-created\n(Kafka Topic)" as InputPipe #LightBlue
participant "🔄 OrderCreatedListener\n@Filter" as Filter1 #LightGreen
participant "📤 Internal Queue\n(ItemOrderedEvent)" as Pipe1 #LightYellow
participant "🔄 StockReservation\n@Filter" as Filter2 #LightGreen
participant "📤 Internal Queue\n(ReservationOutcome)" as Pipe2 #LightYellow
participant "🔄 ReservationOutcomePublisher\n@Filter" as Filter3 #LightGreen
participant "📤 stock-reserved\n(Kafka Topic)" as SuccessPipe #LightCyan
participant "📤 stock-failed\n(Kafka Topic)" as FailurePipe #LightCoral
participant "🔄 StockReplenishment\n@Filter" as Filter4 #LightGreen
participant "📡 Supplier API\n(External)" as ExternalPipe #LightGray

== Stage 1: Order Splitting ==

InputPipe -> Filter1: OrderCreatedEvent
activate Filter1

note right of Filter1
**Split Order into Items**
• 1 order → N item events
• Preserve order context
end note

Filter1 -> Pipe1: ItemOrderedEvent (Item 1)
Filter1 -> Pipe1: ItemOrderedEvent (Item 2)
Filter1 -> Pipe1: ItemOrderedEvent (Item N...)

deactivate Filter1

== Stage 2: Stock Reservation ==

Pipe1 -> Filter2: ItemOrderedEvent
activate Filter2

note right of Filter2
**Reserve Stock**
• Query inventory
• Check availability
• Update stock levels
end note

Filter2 -> Filter2: Check Database
Filter2 -> Filter2: Reserve Stock

alt Stock Available
    Filter2 -> Pipe2: Success Outcome
else Stock Unavailable
    Filter2 -> Pipe2: Failure Outcome
end

deactivate Filter2

== Stage 3: Outcome Routing ==

Pipe2 -> Filter3: ReservationOutcome
activate Filter3

note right of Filter3
**Route Results**
• Success → stock-reserved
• Failure → stock-failed
end note

alt Success
    Filter3 -> SuccessPipe: ReservationCompletedEvent
else Failure
    Filter3 -> FailurePipe: ReservationFailedEvent
end

deactivate Filter3

== Stage 4: Replenishment ==

SuccessPipe -> Filter4: ReservationCompletedEvent
activate Filter4

note right of Filter4
**Check Replenishment**
• Compare with thresholds
• Trigger supplier if needed
end note

Filter4 -> Filter4: Check Stock Level

alt Below Threshold
    Filter4 -> ExternalPipe: Replenishment Request
    note right of ExternalPipe
    **Supplier API**
    REST call to reorder stock
    end note
else Above Threshold
    note right of Filter4
    No action needed
    end note
end

deactivate Filter4

@enduml